{"title_page": "List of Asian Indoor Games records in athletics", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe [[Asian Indoor Games]] is a biennial event which began in [[2005 Asian Indoor Games|2005]]. The [[Olympic Council of Asia]] accepts only athletes who are representing one of the organisation's member states (most of which are within [[Asia]]) and recognises records set at editions of the Asian Indoor Games. The Games records in [[athletics (sport)|athletics]] are the best marks set in competitions at the Games.\n\n==Men's records==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; width: 95%;\"\n!Event\n!Record\n!Name\n!Nationality\n!Date\n!Games\n!Ref\n|-\n|[[60 metres|60 m]]\n|6.54\n|[[Samuel Francis (athlete)|Samuel Francis]]\n|{{flagIOC2|QAT|2007 Asian Indoor Games}}\n|30 October 2007\n|[[Indoor athletics at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games|2007 Macau]]\n|\n|-\n|[[400 metres|400 m]]\n|45.68\n|[[Abdalelah Haroun]]\n|{{flagIOC2|QAT|2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games}}\n|19 September 2017\n|[[Indoor athletics at the 2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games|2017 Ashgabat]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=400m Results|url=http://ashgabat2017.com/atos/ashgabat17/resAG2017/pdf/AG2017/AT/AG2017_AT_C73A_ATM004101.pdf|website=ashgabat2017.com|date=19 September 2017|accessdate=24 September 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[800 metres|800 m]]\n|1:48.48\n|[[Sajjad Moradi]]\n|{{flagIOC2|IRI|2009 Asian Indoor Games}}\n|2 November 2009\n|[[Indoor athletics at the 2009 Asian Indoor Games|2009 Hanoi]]\n|\n|-\n|[[1500 metres|1500 m]]\n|3:42.36\n|[[Thamer Kamal Ali]]\n|{{flagIOC2|QAT|2009 Asian Indoor Games}}\n|2 November 2009\n|[[Indoor athletics at the 2009 Asian Indoor Games|2009 Hanoi]]\n|\n|-\n|[[3000 metres|3000 m]]\n|8:00.40\n|[[James Kwalia]]\n|{{flagIOC2|QAT|2009 Asian Indoor Games}}\n|1 November 2009\n|[[Indoor athletics at the 2009 Asian Indoor Games|2009 Hanoi]]\n|\n|-\n|[[60 metre hurdles|60 m hurdles]]\n|7.66\n|[[Ahmed Al-Muwallad]]\n|{{flagIOC2|KSA|2017 Asian Ind